      "text": [
        "1690 - وَ قَالَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «لِكُلِّ شَيْءٍ ثَمَرَةٌ وَ ثَمَرَةُ اَلْمَعْرُوفِ تَعْجِيلُهُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1690 - Abu Ja'far (as) said:\n\"Everything has a fruit, and the fruit of goodness is hastening to perform it.\""
        ]
      }
    }
